quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  26,1,S.M. Toor-e-Sina and Moses - Recall Mount Sinai where Moses was given the Statute Book
  26,2,"Now these are verses of the Final Statute Book, clear in itself and clearly showing the Truth"
  26,3,"(O Prophet) Will you, (in your compassion), torment yourself to death because they refuse to believe in it"
  26,4,"Had We so Willed, We could have sent down to them a Sign from the sky, to which they would have bent their necks in humility. (But, that is not Our Design. We expect them to use their reason)"
  26,5,"And so whenever a Reminder comes to them from the Beneficent, they turn away from it"
  26,6,Thus indeed have they rejected this Message. But in time they will come to understand what it was that they ridiculed
  26,7,Do they not see the earth how much of every fruitful kind We cause to grow therein
  26,8,"This is indeed a Sign, yet most of them are not believers (in the Almightiness of their Lord)"
  26,9,"But, verily, your Lord is Almighty, Merciful. (Whether they believe or not He provides them with means of sustenance)"
  26,10,"And recall when your Lord called Moses, \"Go to the nation of the oppressors"
  26,11,To the people of Pharaoh so that they may walk aright
  26,12,"Moses said, \"My Lord! I am afraid they will accuse me of lying"
  26,13,"I shall be embarrassed and I might not speak confidently, so send for Aaron to help me"
  26,14,"And they stick a charge against me, so I fear they will kill me"
  26,15,"Allah said, \"Nay! Both of you go with Our Messages. We are with you"
  26,16,"Go together to Pharaoh and say, \"We are Messengers from the Lord of the Worlds"
  26,17,"And, \"Let the Children of Israel go with us"
  26,18,"Pharaoh said to Moses, \"Did we not rear you as a child among us? And you lived with us many years of your life"
  26,19,"And you did what you did, killing a man from our nation. You are of the ungrateful"